Do you want to drop the selected Foreign Key(s)?

There in no direct way to ALTER a Foreign Key in MySQL. SQLyog will drop the existing one and create a new one using the existing name for the key. If necessary preconditions for a Foreign Key (matching data types, appropriate indexes etc.) are not met, the create process will fail. The result will be that existing FK is dropped and no new one is created. You can avoid this by specifying a new name for the key.
